      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Cardinal John O'Connor's body will lie in state in St. Patrick's Cathedral until the funeral, which will likely be at 2 p.m. Monday, said Joseph Zwilling, the archdiocese spokesman. ''There will be opportunities for public mourning and for people to come and pay their respects,'' he said.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Cardinal John O'Connor's body will lie in state in St. Patrick's Cathedral until the funeral, which will likely be at 2 p.m. Monday, said Joseph Zwilling, the archdiocese spokesman. ''There will be opportunities for public mourning and for people to come and pay their respects,'' he said.</p>
        <p>He said Masses would be scheduled to give ''as many people as possible'' the opportunity to attend.</p>
        <p>DEATH OF A CARDINAL</p>
